<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,597,948]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,705,731]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Host plant</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1822" box="[340,467,705,731]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Spach) Turcz. ex Rupr." authorityName="Rupr." baseAuthorityName="Spach" box="[478,909,705,732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis box="[478,629,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Alnus hirsuta</emphasis>
(Spach) Turcz. ex Rupr.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Callier" authorityName="Callier" box="[920,1214,705,731]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="matsumurae">
<emphasis box="[920,1130,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Alnus matsumurae</emphasis>
Callier
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="123 - 128" refId="ref77685" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (1999) Host-plant records for six pamphiliine sawflies (Hymenoptera: Pamphiliidae) in Hokkaido, Japan. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 25, 123 - 128." type="journal article" year="1999">Shinohara &amp; Hara 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 2005; Shinohara 2005). Shinohara &amp; Okutani’s (1983) record of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Callier) D. Love" authorityName="D. Love" baseAuthorityName="Callier" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="viridis" subSpecies="maximowiczii">
<emphasis box="[967,1111,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Alnus viridis</emphasis>
(Chaix) Lam. et DC. subsp. 
<emphasis box="[151,305,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">maximowiczii</emphasis>
(Callier) D. Löve
</taxonomicName>
is probably erroneous (Shinohara 2005).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,597,948]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,813,839]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is known only from Sakhalin and 
<collectingCountry box="[857,924,814,840]" name="Japan" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The larva feeds on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Hara" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[1156,1220,813,839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1156,1220,813,839]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Alnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
solitarily, rolling a leaf edge below. The egg is deposited on the underside of the leaf (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H." box="[904,1208,849,875]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="23 - 28" refId="ref78244" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H. (2006) Some biological features of three Pamphilius species (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) feeding on alders in Nagano Prefecture, Honshu, Japan: Results of rearing experiments in 2004 / 2005. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 32, 23 - 28." type="journal article" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1227,1437,849,875]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[439,570,885,911]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
